         <abstract>
            <p>This paper describes a multiple shaker control system developed at Sandia National Laboratories for driving a single test item with random excitation. The system allows for cross-coupled mechanical systems with partially coherent control points. The system uses time-domain randomization to generate the continuous Gaussian drive signals.</p>
